Post installation script developed for Ubuntu 24.04, based on my use of programs, configurations and customizations. 

Link to download the ISO: https://ubuntu.com/download/desktop/thank-you?version=24.04&architecture=amd64&lts=true

o que este script faz?

Install codecs, fonts and tweaks:
`ubuntu-restricted-extras `
`amd64-microcode`
`font-manager`
``gnome-browser-connector ``
``gnome-boxes``
``p7zip-rar``
``zsh``
``fontconfig``
``git``
``docker.io``
``distrobox``
``inkscape``
``gimp``
``gimp-plugin-registry ``

``Adding/Confirming 32-bit architecture``

``Change Firefox Snap to .deb with official Mozilla repository``

``Change Radeon to Amdgpu``

``Install and configure Zsh``

Make all improvements:

```curl -o pos_install_complete.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/phaleixo/after_install_ubuntu_24.04/main/pos_install_complete.sh && chmod +x pos_install_complete.sh && ./pos_install_complete.sh && rm pos_install_complete.sh```
